51//Switch implementation for pointer types
52#define __CLOVE_SWITCH_BEG(X) \
53 { \
54 size_t* expr = (size_t*)(size_t)X; \
55 if (false) { }
56#define __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(Y) \
57 else if (expr == (size_t*)(size_t)Y)
58#define __CLOVE_SWITCH_DEFAULT() \
59 else
60#define __CLOVE_SWITCH_END() }

266#define __CLOVE_VECTOR_FOREACH(VECTOR_PTR, TYPE, NAME, BODY) \
267 for(size_t __CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(__CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(vector_index_,NAME), __LINE__)=0; __CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(__CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(vector_index_,NAME), __LINE__) < __clove_vector_count(VECTOR_PTR); ++__CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(__CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(vector_index_,NAME), __LINE__)) { \
268 TYPE* NAME = (TYPE*)__clove_vector_get(VECTOR_PTR, __CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(__CLOVE_MACRO_COMBINE(vector_index_,NAME), __LINE__)); \
269 BODY \
270 }

511#pragma region PRIVATE - Assert Decl
512#define __CLOVE_ASSERT_GUARD \
513 if (_this->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED) { return; }\
514 if (_this->file_name == NULL) _this->file_name = __FILE__; \
515 _this->issue.line = __LINE__;
516
517#define __CLOVE_ASSERT_INTEGER_CHECK(mode, exp, act, type, field, test) \
518 bool pass_scenario = false;\
519 if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ) { pass_scenario = exp == act; }\
520 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_NE) { pass_scenario = exp != act; }\
521 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_GT) { pass_scenario = exp > act; }\
522 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_GTE) { pass_scenario = exp >= act; }\
523 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_LT) { pass_scenario = exp < act; }\
524 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_LTE) { pass_scenario = exp <= act; }\
525 if (pass_scenario) _this->result = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_PASSED;\
526 else { \
527 _this->result = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED;\
528 _this->issue.assert = mode;\
529 _this->issue.data_type = type;\
530 _this->issue.expected.field = exp;\
531 _this->issue.actual.field = act;\
532 }

665#define __CLOVE_STRING_LENGTH 256
666#define __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(buffer, buffer_size, assert, exp, act, print_type) \
667{ \
668 char phrase_format[40] = {0}; \
669 if (assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ) __clove_string_sprintf(phrase_format, sizeof(phrase_format), "expected [%s] but was [%s]", print_type, print_type); \
670 else if(assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_NE) __clove_string_sprintf(phrase_format, sizeof(phrase_format), "not expected [%s] but was [%s]", print_type, print_type); \
671 else if(assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_GT) __clove_string_sprintf(phrase_format, sizeof(phrase_format), "expected [%s > %s] but wasn't", print_type, print_type); \
672 else if(assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_GTE) __clove_string_sprintf(phrase_format, sizeof(phrase_format), "expected [%s >= %s] but wasn't", print_type, print_type); \
673 else if(assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_LT) __clove_string_sprintf(phrase_format, sizeof(phrase_format), "expected [%s < %s] but wasn't", print_type, print_type); \
674 else if(assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_LTE) __clove_string_sprintf(phrase_format, sizeof(phrase_format), "expected [%s <= %s] but wasn't", print_type, print_type); \
675 __clove_string_sprintf(buffer, buffer_size, phrase_format, exp, act); \
676}

914char* __clove_path_concat(const char* path1, const char* path2, const char separator) {
915 size_t count = __clove_string_length(path1) + 1 + __clove_string_length(path2) + 1;
916 char* path = __CLOVE_MEMORY_CALLOC_TYPE_N(char, count);
917
918 __clove_string_strcat(path, count, path1);
919 __clove_string_strncat(path, count, &separator, 1);
920 __clove_string_strcat(path, count, path2);
921
922 __clove_string_replace_char(path, '/', separator);
923 __clove_string_replace_char(path, '\\', separator);
924
925 return path;
926}
927
928const char* __clove_path_relative(const char* abs_path, const char* base_path) {
929 if (!__clove_string_startswith(abs_path, base_path)) return abs_path;
930
931 size_t base_path_length = __clove_string_length(base_path);
932 const char* result = abs_path + base_path_length;
933 if (__clove_string_startswith(result, __CLOVE_PATH_SEPARATOR_STR)) {
934 result += 1;
935 }
936 return result;
937}

939char* __clove_path_rel_to_abs_exec_path(const char* rel_path) {
940 const char* base_path = __clove_utils_get_exec_abs_basepath();
941 char* abs_path = __clove_path_concat(base_path, rel_path, __CLOVE_PATH_SEPARATOR);
942 return abs_path;
943}

945bool __clove_path_is_relative(const char* path) {
946 if (__clove_string_startswith(path, "\\")) return false; //windows (match the main unit)
947 if (__clove_string_length(path) > 2 && path[1] == ':') return false; //windows (contains unit:)
948 if (__clove_string_startswith(path, "/")) return false; //unix or Windows
949 return true;
950}
951
952bool __clove_path_is_absolute(const char* path) {
953 return !__clove_path_is_relative(path);
954}

956void __clove_path_to_os(char* path) {
957 __clove_string_replace_char(path, '/', __CLOVE_PATH_SEPARATOR);
958 __clove_string_replace_char(path, '\\', __CLOVE_PATH_SEPARATOR);
959}
960
961char* __clove_path_basepath(const char* path) {
962 char temp_path[__CLOVE_PATH_MAX_LEN];
963 __clove_string_strcpy(temp_path, sizeof(temp_path), path);
964
965 //Remove last path separator character if any
966 bool last_char_is_win = __clove_string_endswith(path, "\\");
967 bool last_char_is_uni = __clove_string_endswith(path, "/");
968 if (last_char_is_win || last_char_is_uni) {
969 size_t last_index = __clove_string_length(temp_path) - 1;
970 temp_path[last_index] = '\0';
971 }
972
973 // Find the last path separator character in the input path.
974 int last_char_win = __clove_string_last_indexof(temp_path, '\\');
975 int last_char_uni = __clove_string_last_indexof(temp_path, '/'); //or unix or win eventually
976 int last_char_index = last_char_win > last_char_uni ? last_char_win : last_char_uni;
977
978 // If there are no separators in the path, return the current directory path.
979 char* result = NULL;
980 if (last_char_index < 0) {
981 static char dot_path[3] = { '.', __CLOVE_PATH_SEPARATOR, '\0' };
982 result = __clove_string_strdup(dot_path);
983 } else {
984 // Calculate base path length based on the position of the last path separator.
985 size_t base_length = ((size_t)last_char_index) + 1;
986 char* base_path = __CLOVE_MEMORY_CALLOC_TYPE_N(char, base_length);
987 __clove_string_strncpy(base_path, base_length, temp_path, base_length - 1);
988 __clove_path_to_os(base_path);
989 result = base_path;
990 }
991
992 return result;
993}

995bool __clove_path_exists(const char* path) {
996 struct stat buffer;
997 return stat(path, &buffer) == 0;
998}
999
1000char* __clove_path_to_absolute(const char* rel_path) {
1001 char* result = NULL;
1002#if _WIN32
1003 result = __CLOVE_MEMORY_MALLOC_TYPE_N(char, _MAX_PATH);
1004
1005 char* discarded = _fullpath(result, rel_path, _MAX_PATH );
1006 __CLOVE_UNUSED_VAR(discarded); //fix "warning C6031: Return value ignored: '_fullpath'."
1007#else
1008 result = __CLOVE_MEMORY_MALLOC_TYPE_N(char, PATH_MAX);
1009 if (__clove_path_exists(rel_path)) {
1010 realpath(rel_path, result); // NULL
1011 } else {
1012 if (__clove_path_is_absolute(rel_path)) {
1013 __clove_string_strcpy(result, PATH_MAX, rel_path);
1014 } else { //relative
1015 realpath(".", result); //getcwd
1016 if (!__clove_string_endswith(result, "/")) {
1017 __clove_string_strcat(result, PATH_MAX, "/");
1018 }
1019 if (__clove_string_startswith(rel_path, "./")) {
1020 rel_path = rel_path + 2;
1021 }
1022
1023 __clove_string_strcat(result, PATH_MAX, rel_path);
1024 }
1025 }
1026
1027/*
1028 //case where rel_path not really exists on fs
1029 //(in this case only the first subpath of the rel_path is added by realpath)
1030 if (!__clove_string_endswith(result, rel_path)) {
1031 if (__clove_path_is_absolute(rel_path)) {
1032 __clove_string_strcpy(result, PATH_MAX, rel_path);
1033 } else { //relative
1034 realpath(".", result);
1035 if (!__clove_string_endswith(result, "/")) {
1036 __clove_string_strcat(result, PATH_MAX, "/");
1037 }
1038 __clove_string_strcat(result, PATH_MAX, rel_path);
1039 }
1040 }
1041*/
1042#endif
1043 return result;
1044}

1162bool __clove_string_startswith(const char* str1, const char* prefix) {
1163 if (!str1 || !prefix) return false;
1164 size_t prefix_len = __clove_string_length(prefix);
1165 if (prefix_len == 0) {
1166 size_t str_len = __clove_string_length(str1);
1167 if (str_len == 0) return true;
1168 else return false;
1169 }
1170 return __clove_string_strncmp(str1, prefix, prefix_len);
1171}
1172
1173bool __clove_string_endswith(const char* str, const char* suffix) {
1174 if (!str || !suffix) return false;
1175 size_t str_len = __clove_string_length(str);
1176 size_t suf_len = __clove_string_length(suffix);
1177 if (suf_len > str_len) return false;
1178 return __clove_string_strncmp(str + str_len - suf_len, suffix, suf_len);
1179}

1260char* __clove_string_escape(const char* string) {
1261 size_t str_len = __clove_string_length(string);
1262 size_t esc_len = str_len * 2 + 1; //worst case where each char needs escape
1263 char* escaped = __CLOVE_MEMORY_CALLOC_TYPE_N(char, esc_len);
1264
1265 size_t esc_index = 0;
1266 for (size_t str_index = 0; str_index < str_len; ++str_index) {
1267 char c = string[str_index];
1268 switch (c)
1269 {
1270 case '\b':
1271 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1272 escaped[esc_index] = 'b';
1273 break;
1274 case '\f':
1275 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1276 escaped[esc_index] = 'f';
1277 break;
1278 case '\n':
1279 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1280 escaped[esc_index] = 'n';
1281 break;
1282 case '\r':
1283 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1284 escaped[esc_index] = 'r';
1285 break;
1286 case '\t':
1287 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1288 escaped[esc_index] = 't';
1289 break;
1290 case '"':
1291 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1292 escaped[esc_index] = '"';
1293 break;
1294 case '\\':
1295 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1296 escaped[esc_index] = '\\';
1297 break;
1298 default:
1299 escaped[esc_index] = c;
1300 break;
1301 }
1302 esc_index++;
1303 }
1304 return escaped;
1305}

1307char* __clove_string_csv_escape(const char* string) {
1308 size_t str_len = __clove_string_length(string);
1309 size_t esc_len = str_len * 2 + 2 + 1; //worst case where each char need escape + 2 for string who need to be enclosed in double quotes
1310 char* escaped = __CLOVE_MEMORY_CALLOC_TYPE_N(char, esc_len);
1311
1312 bool has_comma = false;
1313 if (__clove_string_contains(string, ",")) has_comma = true;
1314
1315 size_t esc_index = has_comma ? 1 : 0;
1316 for (size_t str_index = 0; str_index < str_len; ++str_index) {
1317 char c = string[str_index];
1318 switch (c)
1319 {
1320 case '\b':
1321 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1322 escaped[esc_index] = 'b';
1323 break;
1324 case '\f':
1325 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1326 escaped[esc_index] = 'f';
1327 break;
1328 case '\n':
1329 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1330 escaped[esc_index] = 'n';
1331 break;
1332 case '\r':
1333 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1334 escaped[esc_index] = 'r';
1335 break;
1336 case '\t':
1337 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1338 escaped[esc_index] = 't';
1339 break;
1340 case '"':
1341 escaped[esc_index++] = '"'; //csv escape char for double quote
1342 escaped[esc_index] = '"';
1343 break;
1344 case '\\':
1345 escaped[esc_index++] = '\\';
1346 escaped[esc_index] = '\\';
1347 break;
1348 default:
1349 escaped[esc_index] = c;
1350 break;
1351 }
1352 esc_index++;
1353 }
1354
1355 if (has_comma) {
1356 escaped[0] = '"';
1357 escaped[esc_index] = '"';
1358 }
1359
1360 return escaped;
1361}

1363void __clove_string_ellipse(const char* string, size_t str_len, size_t pos, char* out, size_t out_size) {
1364 if (str_len == 1) {
1365 out[0] = '\0';
1366 return;
1367 }
1368 if (str_len <= out_size-1) {
1369 __clove_string_strcpy(out, out_size, string);
1370 return;
1371 }
1372
1373 bool left_ellipse = false;
1374 bool right_ellipse = false;
1375 if (pos >= 4) {
1376 left_ellipse = true;
1377 }
1378
1379 if (str_len-1 - pos >= 4) {
1380 right_ellipse = true;
1381 }
1382
1383 size_t out_start = 0;
1384 size_t start_index = 0;
1385 size_t out_end = out_size - 1;
1386
1387 if (left_ellipse) {
1388 out_start = 3;
1389 start_index = right_ellipse ? pos - 3 : str_len - 12;
1390 out[0] = '.'; out[1] = '.'; out[2] = '.';
1391 }
1392
1393 if (right_ellipse) {
1394 out_end -= 3;
1395 out[out_end] = '.'; out[out_end + 1] = '.'; out[out_end + 2] = '.';
1396 }
1397 out[out_size - 1] = '\0';
1398
1399 size_t to_copy = out_end - out_start;
1400
1401 //Copia stringa
1402 for (size_t i = 0; i < to_copy; ++i) {
1403 out[out_start + i] = string[start_index + i];
1404 }
1405}

1408 size_t size = __clove_string_length(str);
1409 for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
1410 if (str[i] == src_chr) {
1411 str[i] = dst_chr;
1412 }
1413 }

1416void __clove_string_pad_right(char* dest, size_t dest_size, size_t str_target_len) {
1417 //capped by dest buffer size, taking account space of null terminator
1418 if (str_target_len >= dest_size) str_target_len = dest_size - 1;
1419
1420 size_t str_len = __clove_string_length(dest);
1421
1422 //Compute padding length avoiding negative result
1423 size_t pad_len = 0;
1424 if (str_target_len > str_len) pad_len = str_target_len - str_len;
1425
1426 char* pad_beg = dest + str_len;
1427 char* pad_end = dest + str_len + pad_len;
1428
1429 __clove_memory_memset(pad_beg , pad_len, '.');
1430 *pad_end = '\0';
1431}

1526#pragma region PRIVATE - Time Impl
1527__clove_time_t __clove_time_sub(__clove_time_t* t1, __clove_time_t* t2) {
1528 __clove_time_t result;
1529 result.seconds = t1->seconds - t2->seconds;
1530 result.nanos_after_seconds = t1->nanos_after_seconds - t2->nanos_after_seconds;
1531 if (result.seconds > 0 && result.nanos_after_seconds < 0) {
1532 result.seconds--;
1533 result.nanos_after_seconds += __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_SEC;
1534 }
1535 else if (result.seconds < 0 && result.nanos_after_seconds > 0) {
1536 result.seconds++;
1537 result.nanos_after_seconds -= __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_SEC;
1538 }
1539 return result;
1540}
1541
1542__clove_time_t __clove_time_sum(__clove_time_t* t1, __clove_time_t* t2) {
1543 __clove_time_t result;
1544 result.seconds = t1->seconds + t2->seconds;
1545 result.nanos_after_seconds = t1->nanos_after_seconds + t2->nanos_after_seconds;
1546 if (result.nanos_after_seconds >= __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_SEC) {
1547 result.seconds++;
1548 result.nanos_after_seconds -= __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_SEC;
1549 }
1550 return result;
1551}
1552
1553unsigned long long __clove_time_to_millis(__clove_time_t* t) {
1554 unsigned long long result = 0;
1555 result += t->seconds * __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_MILLIS_PER_SEC;
1556 result += t->nanos_after_seconds / __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_MILLIS;
1557 return result;
1558}
1559
1560unsigned long long __clove_time_to_nanos(__clove_time_t* t) {
1561 unsigned long long result = 0;
1562 result += t->seconds * __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_SEC;
1563 result += t->nanos_after_seconds;
1564 return result;
1565}

1567#ifdef _WIN32
1568#include <windows.h>
1569#include <time.h>
1570__clove_time_t __clove_time_now(void) {
1571 static bool first_time = true;
1572 static LARGE_INTEGER count_per_sec;
1573 __clove_time_t result;
1574 result.seconds = 0;
1575 result.nanos_after_seconds = 0;
1576
1577 if (first_time) {
1578 first_time = false;
1579 if (QueryPerformanceFrequency(&count_per_sec) == 0) {
1580 return result;
1581 }
1582 }
1583
1584 LARGE_INTEGER count;
1585 if (QueryPerformanceCounter(&count) == 0) {
1586 return result;
1587 }
1588
1589 result.seconds = count.QuadPart / count_per_sec.QuadPart;
1590 result.nanos_after_seconds = ((count.QuadPart % count_per_sec.QuadPart) * __CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_SEC) / count_per_sec.QuadPart;
1591 return result;
1592}

1599
1600 __clove_time_t result;
1601 result.seconds = time_data.tv_sec;
1602 result.nanos_after_seconds = time_data.tv_nsec;
1603 return result;
1604}

1622void __clove_stack_push(__clove_stack_t* stack, size_t item) {
1623 if (stack->count == stack->capacity) {
1624 stack->capacity *= 2;
1625 stack->items = (unsigned char*)__clove_memory_realloc(stack->items, stack->item_size * stack->capacity);
1626 }
1627 size_t byte_index = stack->count * stack->item_size;
1628 size_t* item_ptr = (size_t*)&(stack->items[byte_index]);
1629 *item_ptr = item;
1630 stack->count++;
1631}

1634 if (stack->count == 0) return 0; //shouldn't happen
1635
1636 size_t byte_index = (stack->count - 1) * stack->item_size;
1637 size_t* item_ptr = (size_t*)&(stack->items[byte_index]);
1638 stack->count--;
1639 return *item_ptr;
1640}

1647 stack->count = 0;
1648 stack->item_size = 0;
1649}

1706void __clove_vector_add_all(__clove_vector_t* vector, const __clove_vector_t* other) {
1707 if (vector->item_size != other->item_size) return;
1708
1709 size_t vector_free_slots = vector->capacity - vector->count;
1710 if (vector_free_slots < other->count)
1711 {
1712 vector->capacity = vector->count + other->count;
1713 vector->items = (unsigned char*)__clove_memory_realloc(vector->items, vector->item_size * vector->capacity);
1714 }
1715
1716 size_t byte_index = vector->count * vector->item_size;
1717
1718 void* dest = (void*)&(vector->items[byte_index]);
1719 size_t dest_size = (vector->capacity - vector->count) * vector->item_size;
1720 void* src = other->items;
1721 size_t src_size = other->count * other->item_size;
1722 __clove_memory_memcpy(dest, dest_size, src, src_size);
1723
1724 vector->count += other->count;
1725}

1770
1771//QuickSort
1772size_t __clove_vector_quicksort_partition(__clove_vector_t* vector, int (*comparator)(void*, void*), size_t start_index, size_t end_index) {
1773 size_t pivot_index = start_index;
1774 size_t left_index = start_index;
1775 size_t right_index = end_index;
1776
1777 void* item = NULL;
1778 void* pivot = NULL;
1779 while (left_index < right_index) {
1780 //Moving pivot to right
1781 bool item_is_gte = true;
1782 while (item_is_gte && pivot_index < right_index) {
1783 item = __clove_vector_get(vector, right_index);
1784 pivot = __clove_vector_get(vector, pivot_index);
1785 item_is_gte = (comparator(item, pivot) >= 0);
1786 if (item_is_gte) right_index--;
1787 }
1788
1789 if (pivot_index != right_index) {
1790 __clove_vector_swap(vector, pivot_index, right_index);
1791 pivot_index = right_index;
1792 }
1793
1794 if (left_index == right_index) break;
1795
1796 //Moving pivot to left
1797 bool item_is_lte = true;
1798 while (item_is_lte && pivot_index > left_index) {
1799 item = __clove_vector_get(vector, left_index);
1800 pivot = __clove_vector_get(vector, pivot_index);
1801 item_is_lte = (comparator(item, pivot) <= 0);
1802 if (item_is_lte) left_index++;
1803 }
1804
1805 if (pivot_index != left_index) {
1806 __clove_vector_swap(vector, pivot_index, left_index);
1807 pivot_index = left_index;
1808 }
1809 }
1810 return pivot_index;
1811}
1812
1813void __clove_vector_quicksort_iterative(__clove_vector_t* vector, int (*comparator)(void*, void*), size_t start_index, size_t end_index) {
1814 __clove_stack_t index_pairs_stack;
1815 __clove_stack_init(&index_pairs_stack, vector->count);
1816
1817 __clove_stack_push(&index_pairs_stack, start_index);
1818 __clove_stack_push(&index_pairs_stack, end_index);
1819
1820 while (!__clove_stack_is_empty(&index_pairs_stack)) {
1821 end_index = __clove_stack_pop(&index_pairs_stack);
1822 start_index = __clove_stack_pop(&index_pairs_stack);
1823
1824 if (start_index >= end_index) continue;
1825
1826 //find a pivot and put it in the right position
1827 size_t pivot_index = __clove_vector_quicksort_partition(vector, comparator, start_index, end_index);
1828
1829 //left array indexes
1830 if (pivot_index != 0) { //protect size_t overflow (for instance, this happens for already sorted items)
1831 __clove_stack_push(&index_pairs_stack, start_index);
1832 __clove_stack_push(&index_pairs_stack, pivot_index - 1);
1833 }
1834
1835 //right array indexes
1836 if (pivot_index != SIZE_MAX) { //protect size_t overflow (for symmetry)
1837 __clove_stack_push(&index_pairs_stack, pivot_index + 1);
1838 __clove_stack_push(&index_pairs_stack, end_index);
1839 }
1840 }
1841 __clove_stack_free(&index_pairs_stack);
1842}
1843
1844void __clove_vector_sort(__clove_vector_t* vector, int (*comparator)(void*, void*)) {
1845 if (vector->count <= 1) return;
1846 __clove_vector_quicksort_iterative(vector, comparator, 0, vector->count - 1);
1847}

1855#pragma region PRIVATE - Map Impl
1856#include <stdlib.h>
1857// Bernstein classic hash
1858size_t __clove_map_hash_djb33x(void *key, size_t keylen) {
1859 size_t hash = 5381;
1860 unsigned char *key_as_num = (unsigned char *)key;
1861 for (size_t i = 0; i < keylen; i++) {
1862 hash = ((hash << 5) + hash) ^ key_as_num[i];
1863 }
1864 return hash;
1865}

1868{

1872 params.item_dtor = NULL;

1874}

1876void __clove_map_init(__clove_map_t* map, __clove_map_params_t* params) {
1877 map->hashmap_size = params->initial_hash_size;
1878 map->hashmap = __CLOVE_MEMORY_CALLOC_TYPE_N(__clove_map_node_t*, map->hashmap_size);
1879 map->hash_funct = params->hash_funct;
1880 map->item_dtor = params->item_dtor;
1881 map->count = 0;
1882}
1883
1884void __clove_map_free(__clove_map_t* map) {
1885 for(size_t i=0; i < map->hashmap_size; ++i) {
1886 if (!map->hashmap[i]) continue;
1887 __clove_map_node_t* node = map->hashmap[i];
1888
1889 __clove_map_node_t* current = node;
1890 while(current) {
1891 __clove_map_node_t* next = current->next;
1892
1893 __clove_memory_free(current->key);
1894 if (map->item_dtor) {
1895 //if dtor set, means map become owner of the item (and its memory)
1896 map->item_dtor(current->value);
1897 __clove_memory_free(current->value);
1898 }
1899 __clove_memory_free(current);
1900
1901 current = next;
1902 }
1903 }
1904 __clove_memory_free(map->hashmap);
1905 map->hashmap = NULL;
1906 map->hashmap_size = 0;
1907 map->count = 0;
1908}

1913
1914bool __clove_map_has_key(__clove_map_t* map, const char* key) {
1915 size_t key_size = __clove_string_length(key);
1916 size_t hash = __clove_map_hash_djb33x((void*)key, key_size);
1917 size_t hash_index = hash % map->hashmap_size;
1918
1919 __clove_map_node_t* node = map->hashmap[hash_index];
1920 while(node) {
1921 if (__clove_string_equal(key, node->key)) return true;
1922 node = node->next;
1923 }
1924 return false;
1925}
1926
1927void __clove_map_put(__clove_map_t* dict, const char* key, void* value) {
1928 size_t key_size = __clove_string_length(key);
1929 size_t hash = dict->hash_funct((void*)key, key_size);
1930 size_t hash_index = hash % dict->hashmap_size;
1931 //Scenario 1: hash(Key) not present
1932 if (!dict->hashmap[hash_index]) {
1933 __clove_map_node_t* node = __CLOVE_MEMORY_MALLOC_TYPE(__clove_map_node_t);
1934 node->key = __clove_string_strdup(key);
1935 node->key_size = key_size;
1936 node->value = value;
1937 node->next = NULL;
1938
1939 dict->hashmap[hash_index] = node;
1940 dict->count++;
1941 } else { //Scenario 2: hash(Key) already present
1942 __clove_map_node_t* node = dict->hashmap[hash_index];
1943 __clove_map_node_t* last = NULL;
1944
1945 //Scenario 2.1: key already exists
1946 while(node) {
1947 last = node;
1948 if (node->key_size == key_size && __clove_string_equal(key, node->key)) {
1949 node->value = value;
1950 return;
1951 }
1952 node = node->next;
1953 }
1954
1955 //Scenario 2.2: key not exists
1956 __clove_map_node_t* new_node = __CLOVE_MEMORY_MALLOC_TYPE(__clove_map_node_t);
1957 new_node->key = __clove_string_strdup(key);
1958 new_node->key_size = key_size;
1959 new_node->value = value;
1960 new_node->next = NULL;
1961
1962 last->next = new_node;
1963 dict->count++;
1964 }
1965
1966}
1967
1968void* __clove_map_get(__clove_map_t* map, const char* key) {
1969 size_t key_size = __clove_string_length(key);
1970 size_t hash = map->hash_funct((void*)key, key_size);
1971 size_t hash_index = hash % map->hashmap_size;
1972
1973 __clove_map_node_t* node = map->hashmap[hash_index];
1974 while(node) {
1975 if (__clove_string_equal(key, node->key)) return node->value;
1976 node = node->next;
1977 }
1978 return NULL;
1979}

1983#include <stdbool.h>
1984#include <string.h>
1985bool __clove_cmdline_next_opt(__clove_cmdline_t* cmdline, const char** opt_out) {
1986 while(cmdline->arg_index < cmdline->argc) {
1987 const char* current = cmdline->argv[cmdline->arg_index];
1988 cmdline->arg_index++;
1989 if (__clove_string_startswith(current, "--") && __clove_string_length(current) > 3) {
1990 *opt_out = current + 2;
1991 return true;
1992 } else if (__clove_string_startswith(current, "-") && __clove_string_length(current) == 2) {
1993 *opt_out = current + 1;
1994 return true;
1995 }
1996 }
1997 return false;
1998}
1999
2000bool __clove_cmdline_next_arg(__clove_cmdline_t* cmdline, const char** arg_out) {
2001 if (cmdline->arg_index >= cmdline->argc) return false;
2002 const char* arg = cmdline->argv[cmdline->arg_index];
2003 if (__clove_string_startswith(arg, "-")) return false;
2004 *arg_out = arg;
2005 cmdline->arg_index++;
2006 return true;
2007}
2008
2009void __clove_cmdline_init(__clove_cmdline_t* cmd, const char** argv, int argc) {
2010 cmd->argv = argv;
2011 cmd->argc = argc;
2012 cmd->arg_index = 1;
2013
2014 __clove_map_params_t params = __clove_map_params_defaulted();
2015 params.item_dtor = __clove_vector_collection_dtor;
2016 __clove_map_init(&cmd->map, &params);
2017
2018 const char* opt;
2019 while(__clove_cmdline_next_opt(cmd, &opt)) {
2020 const char* arg = NULL;
2021 __clove_cmdline_next_arg(cmd, &arg);
2022 __clove_cmdline_add_opt(cmd, opt, arg);
2023 }
2024}

2026void __clove_cmdline_free(__clove_cmdline_t* cmd) {
2027 __clove_map_free(&(cmd->map));
2028 cmd->argv = NULL;
2029 cmd->argc = 0;
2030 cmd->arg_index = 0;
2031}

2033void __clove_cmdline_add_opt(__clove_cmdline_t* cmd, const char* opt, const char* value) {
2034 __clove_vector_t* values;
2035 if (__clove_map_has_key(&(cmd->map), opt)) {
2036 values = (__clove_vector_t*)__clove_map_get(&(cmd->map), opt);
2037 } else {
2038 values = __CLOVE_MEMORY_MALLOC_TYPE(__clove_vector_t);
2039 __CLOVE_VECTOR_INIT(values, char*);
2040 __clove_map_put(&(cmd->map), opt, values);
2041 }
2042 const char* *slot = (const char* *)__clove_vector_add_slot(values);
2043 *slot = value;
2044}

2046bool __clove_cmdline_has_opt(__clove_cmdline_t* cmdline, const char* opt) {

2050 const __clove_vector_t* values = __clove_cmdline_get_opt_values(cmdline, opt);
2051 if (!values || __clove_vector_count(values) == 0) return NULL;
2052 return *(char**)__clove_vector_get(values, 0);
2053}

2103__clove_cmdline_errno_t __clove_cmdline_handle_run_tests(__clove_cmdline_t* cmd) {
2104 if (!__clove_cmdline_has_any_opt(cmd, "t", "run-tests")) return __CLOVE_CMD_ERRNO_UNMANAGED;
2105
2106 const char* opt_report = __clove_cmdline_get_any_opt_value_defaulted(cmd, "r", "report", "pretty");
2107 if (!__clove_string_equal_any(opt_report, 3, "pretty", "json", "csv")) return __CLOVE_CMD_ERRNO_INVALID_PARAM;
2108
2109 const char* opt_detail = __clove_cmdline_get_any_opt_value_defaulted(cmd, "d", "run-detail", "3");
2110 if (!__clove_string_equal_any(opt_detail, 3, "1", "2", "3")) return __CLOVE_CMD_ERRNO_INVALID_PARAM;
2111
2112 const char* opt_out = __clove_cmdline_get_any_opt_value_defaulted(cmd, "o", "output", "stdout");
2113 const char* opt_base_path = __clove_cmdline_get_any_opt_value_defaulted(cmd, "b", "base-path", "");
2114 const bool opt_enable_error = __clove_cmdline_has_any_opt(cmd, "x", "error-on-test-fail");
2115
2116 __clove_vector_t includes;
2117 __clove_cmdline_create_test_expr(cmd, "i", "include", &includes);
2118
2119 __clove_vector_t excludes;
2120 __clove_cmdline_create_test_expr(cmd, "e", "exclude", &excludes);
2121
2122 //Select stream
2123 __clove_stream_t* stream;
2124 if (__clove_string_equal(opt_out, "stdout")) {
2125 stream = (__clove_stream_t*)__clove_stream_console_new();
2126 } else { // file path
2127 const char* report_path;
2128 if (__clove_path_is_relative(opt_out)) {
2129 report_path = __clove_path_rel_to_abs_exec_path(opt_out);
2130 }
2131 else {
2132 report_path = opt_out;
2133 }
2134 stream = (__clove_stream_t*)__clove_stream_file_new(report_path);
2135 }
2136
2137 //Select Report
2138 __clove_report_params_t report_params;
2139
2140 //ensure base path is in os format
2141 char* base_path_fixed = __clove_string_strdup(opt_base_path);
2142 __clove_path_to_os(base_path_fixed);
2143 report_params.tests_base_path = base_path_fixed;
2144
2145 if (__clove_string_equal(opt_detail, "1"))
2146 report_params.report_detail = __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED;
2147 else if (__clove_string_equal(opt_detail, "2"))
2148 report_params.report_detail = __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED_SKIPPED;
2149 else if (__clove_string_equal(opt_detail, "3"))
2150 report_params.report_detail = __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__PASSED_FAILED_SKIPPED;
2151
2152 __clove_report_t* report;
2153 if (__clove_string_equal("json", opt_report)) {
2154 report = (__clove_report_t*)__clove_report_run_tests_json_new(stream, &report_params);
2155 } else if (__clove_string_equal("pretty", opt_report)) {
2156 report = (__clove_report_t*)__clove_report_run_tests_pretty_new(stream, &report_params);
2157 } else if (__clove_string_equal("csv", opt_report)) {
2158 report = (__clove_report_t*)__clove_report_run_tests_csv_new(stream, &report_params);
2159 } else {
2160 //Just to avoid compile warnings. This can never happen because of validation did before.
2161 return __CLOVE_CMD_ERRNO_UNMANAGED;
2162 }
2163
2164 //Run report
2165 int run_result = __clove_run_tests_with_report(report, &includes, &excludes);
2166
2167 //Clean
2168 report->free(report);
2169 stream->free(stream);
2170 __clove_vector_free(&includes);
2171 __clove_vector_free(&excludes);
2172 __clove_memory_free(base_path_fixed);
2173
2174 //Result
2175 if (run_result == 1) return __CLOVE_CMD_ERRNO_GENERIC;
2176 if (run_result == 2 && opt_enable_error) return __CLOVE_CMD_ERRNO_GENERIC;
2177 return __CLOVE_CMD_ERRNO_OK;
2178}

2266void __clove_cmdline_create_test_expr(__clove_cmdline_t* cmd, const char* opt1, const char* opt2, __clove_vector_t* expressions) {
2267 *expressions = __clove_vector_null();
2268
2269 bool has_opt1 = __clove_cmdline_has_opt(cmd, opt1);
2270 bool has_opt2 = __clove_cmdline_has_opt(cmd, opt2);
2271 if ( !has_opt1 && !has_opt2) return;
2272
2273 __clove_vector_t values;
2274 __CLOVE_VECTOR_INIT(&values, char*);
2275
2276 if (has_opt1) {
2277 const __clove_vector_t* values1 = __clove_cmdline_get_opt_values(cmd, opt1);
2278 __clove_vector_add_all(&values, values1);
2279 }
2280 if (has_opt2) {
2281 const __clove_vector_t* values2 = __clove_cmdline_get_opt_values(cmd, opt2);
2282 __clove_vector_add_all(&values, values2);
2283 }
2284
2285 size_t values_count = __clove_vector_count(&values);
2286 __CLOVE_VECTOR_INIT_CAPACITY(expressions, __clove_test_expr_t, values_count);
2287
2288 __CLOVE_VECTOR_FOREACH(&values, char*, expr_str, {
2289 __clove_test_expr_t expr;
2290 __clove_test_expr_init(&expr, *expr_str);
2291
2292 __CLOVE_VECTOR_ADD(expressions, __clove_test_expr_t, expr);
2293 });
2294
2295 __clove_vector_free(&values);
2296}

2402void __clove_assert_float(__clove_assert_check_e check_mode, float expected, float result, unsigned char precision, __clove_test_t* _this) {
2403 bool pass_scenario = false;
2404 if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ) { pass_scenario = fabsf(expected - result) <= __clove_math_decimalf(precision); }
2405 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_NE) { pass_scenario = fabsf(expected - result) > __clove_math_decimalf(precision); }
2406 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_GT) { pass_scenario = expected > result; }
2407 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_GTE) { pass_scenario = expected >= result; }
2408 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_LT) { pass_scenario = expected < result; }
2409 else if (check_mode == __CLOVE_ASSERT_LTE) { pass_scenario = expected <= result; }
2410 if (pass_scenario) {
2411 _this->result = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_PASSED;
2412 }
2413 else {
2414 _this->result = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED;
2415 _this->issue.assert = check_mode;
2416 _this->issue.data_type = __CLOVE_GENERIC_FLOAT;
2417 _this->issue.expected._float = expected;
2418 _this->issue.actual._float = result;
2419 _this->issue.floating_precision = precision;
2420 }

2497#include <windows.h>
2498#include <stdbool.h>
2499#ifndef ENABLE_VIRTUAL_TERMINAL_PROCESSING
2500#define ENABLE_VIRTUAL_TERMINAL_PROCESSING 0x0004
2501#endif
2502bool __clove_stream_console_has_ansi_support(__clove_stream_t* stream) {
2503 __CLOVE_UNUSED_VAR(stream);
2504
2505 DWORD outMode = 0, inMode = 0;
2506 HANDLE stdoutHandle = GetStdHandle(STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE);
2507 HANDLE stdinHandle = GetStdHandle(STD_INPUT_HANDLE);
2508
2509 if (stdoutHandle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE || stdinHandle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) {
2510 //exit(GetLastError());
2511 return false;
2512 }
2513
2514 if (!GetConsoleMode(stdoutHandle, &outMode) || !GetConsoleMode(stdinHandle, &inMode)) {
2515 //exit(GetLastError());
2516 return false;
2517 }
2518
2519 // Enable ANSI escape codes
2520 outMode |= ENABLE_VIRTUAL_TERMINAL_PROCESSING;
2521
2522 // Set stdin as no echo and unbuffered
2523 inMode &= ~(ENABLE_ECHO_INPUT | ENABLE_LINE_INPUT);
2524
2525 if (!SetConsoleMode(stdoutHandle, outMode) || !SetConsoleMode(stdinHandle, inMode)) {
2526 //exit(GetLastError());
2527 return false;
2528 }
2529 return true;
2530}
2531#else
2532#include <stdbool.h>
2533#include <unistd.h>

2535 __CLOVE_UNUSED_VAR(stream);
2536
2537 if (isatty(STDOUT_FILENO)) {
2538 // standard output is a tty
2539 return true;
2540 }
2541 return false;
2542}
2543#endif //_WIN32

2658#pragma region PRIVATE - Report Impl
2659void __clove_test_expr_init(__clove_test_expr_t* expr, const char* expr_str) {
2660 const char* dot_begin = __clove_string_strstr(expr_str, ".");
2661 if (dot_begin) {
2662 const size_t expr_len = __clove_string_length(expr_str);
2663 const size_t suite_len = dot_begin - expr_str;
2664 const size_t test_len = expr_str + expr_len-1 - dot_begin;
2665 if (suite_len == 0) expr->suite_view = __clove_string_view_from_str("");
2666 else expr->suite_view = __clove_string_view_from_be(expr_str, dot_begin - 1);
2667
2668 if (test_len == 0) expr->test_view = __clove_string_view_from_str("");
2669 else expr->test_view = __clove_string_view_from_str(dot_begin + 1);
2670 } else {
2671 expr->suite_view = __clove_string_view_from_str(expr_str);
2672 expr->test_view = __clove_string_view_from_str("*");
2673 }
2674}
2675
2676bool __clove_test_expr_validate_vw(const __clove_string_view_t* match, const __clove_string_view_t* view) {
2677 if (__clove_string_view_strequals(match, "*")) return true;
2678 const size_t match_len = __clove_string_view_length(match);
2679 if (match_len == 0) return false;
2680 const char* match_start = __clove_string_view_begin(match);
2681 const char* match_end = __clove_string_view_end(match);
2682
2683 bool start_asterisk = match_start[0] == '*';
2684 bool end_asterisk = match_end[0] == '*';
2685 if (start_asterisk && end_asterisk) {
2686 if (match_len <= 2) return false;
2687 __clove_string_view_t fixture = __clove_string_view_from_be(match_start+1, match_end-1);
2688 return __clove_string_view_contains(view, &fixture);
2689 }
2690 if (start_asterisk) {
2691 return __clove_string_view_nendswith(view, match, 1);
2692 }
2693 if (end_asterisk) {
2694 return __clove_string_view_ncmp(match, view, __clove_string_view_length(match)-1);
2695 }
2696 return __clove_string_view_equals(match, view);
2697}
2698
2699bool __clove_test_expr_validate(__clove_test_expr_t* expr, const __clove_string_view_t* suite, const __clove_string_view_t* test) {
2700 if (!__clove_test_expr_validate_vw(&(expr->suite_view), suite)) return false;
2701 if (!__clove_test_expr_validate_vw(&(expr->test_view), test)) return false;
2702 return true;
2703}

2725void __clove_report_pretty_start(__clove_report_t* _this, __clove_vector_t* suites, size_t test_count) {
2726 __clove_report_pretty_t* report = (__clove_report_pretty_t*)_this;
2727 report->start_time = __clove_time_now();
2728 report->max_test_digits = (unsigned int)snprintf(NULL, 0U, "%zu", test_count);
2729 report->test_count = test_count;
2730
2731 bool activated = report->stream->has_ansi_support(report->stream);
2732 if (activated) {
2733 report->labels.info = "[\x1b[1;34mINFO\x1b[0m]";
2734 report->labels.warn = "[\x1b[33mWARN\x1b[0m]";
2735 report->labels.erro = "[\x1b[1;31mERRO\x1b[0m]";
2736 report->labels.pass = "[\x1b[1;32mPASS\x1b[0m]";
2737 report->labels.skip = "[\x1b[33mSKIP\x1b[0m]";
2738 report->labels.fail = "[\x1b[1;31mFAIL\x1b[0m]";
2739 }
2740 else {
2741 report->labels.info = "[INFO]";
2742 report->labels.warn = "[WARN]";
2743 report->labels.erro = "[ERRO]";
2744 report->labels.pass = "[PASS]";
2745 report->labels.skip = "[SKIP]";
2746 report->labels.fail = "[FAIL]";
2747 }
2748
2749 const char* level_str = "<unknown>";
2750 if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__PASSED_FAILED_SKIPPED) {
2751 level_str = "Full";
2752 } else if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED) {
2753 level_str = "Failed only";
2754 } else if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED_SKIPPED) {
2755 level_str = "Failed + Skipped";
2756 }
2757
2758 size_t longest_suite_and_test_name = 0;
2759 __CLOVE_VECTOR_FOREACH(suites, __clove_suite_t, each_suite, {
2760 size_t suite_length = __clove_string_length(each_suite->name);
2761 __CLOVE_VECTOR_FOREACH(&each_suite->tests, __clove_test_t, each_test, {
2762 size_t test_length = __clove_string_length(each_test->name);
2763
2764 if (longest_suite_and_test_name < suite_length + test_length) {
2765 longest_suite_and_test_name = suite_length + test_length;
2766 }
2767 });
2768 });
2769
2770 //Force minimum length in case of longest suite/name is less
2771 if (longest_suite_and_test_name < 46) longest_suite_and_test_name = 46; //rounded to 50 by next operation
2772
2773 //+1 take into account dot separator (suite.name)
2774 //+3 to have at least 3 more dot after suite.name
2775 report->max_suite_and_test_name_size = longest_suite_and_test_name + 1 + 3;
2776 //max len capping
2777 if (report->max_suite_and_test_name_size > __CLOVE_STRING_LENGTH) report->max_suite_and_test_name_size = __CLOVE_STRING_LENGTH;
2778
2779 size_t suite_count = __clove_vector_count(suites);
2780
2781 report->stream->open(report->stream);
2782 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s Executing Test Runner with detail level: '%s'\n", report->labels.info, level_str);
2783 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s Suites / Tests found: %zu / %zu\n", report->labels.info, suite_count, test_count);
2784}

2797void __clove_report_pretty_end(__clove_report_t* _this, size_t passed, size_t skipped, size_t failed) {
2798 __clove_report_pretty_t* report = (__clove_report_pretty_t*)_this;
2799 __clove_time_t end_time = __clove_time_now();
2800 __clove_time_t diff = __clove_time_sub(&end_time, &(report->start_time));
2801 unsigned long long millis = __clove_time_to_millis(&diff);
2802
2803 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s Total: %zu, Passed: %zu, Failed: %zu, Skipped: %zu\n", report->labels.info, report->test_count, passed, failed, skipped);
2804 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s Run duration: %llu ms\n", report->labels.info, millis);
2805 if (passed == report->test_count) { report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s Run result: SUCCESS :-)\n", report->labels.info); }
2806 else if (failed > 0) { report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s Run result: FAILURE :_(\n", report->labels.erro); }
2807 else if (skipped > 0) { report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s Run result: OK, but some test has been skipped!\n", report->labels.warn); }
2808
2809 report->stream->close(report->stream);
2810}
2811
2812void __clove_report_pretty_end_test(__clove_report_t* _this, __clove_suite_t* suite, __clove_test_t* test, size_t test_number) {
2813 __clove_report_pretty_t* report = (__clove_report_pretty_t*)_this;
2814
2815 bool print_passed = false;
2816 bool print_failed = false;
2817 bool print_skipped = false;
2818 if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__PASSED_FAILED_SKIPPED) {
2819 print_passed = true;
2820 print_failed = true;
2821 print_skipped = true;
2822 } else if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED) {
2823 print_passed = false;
2824 print_failed = true;
2825 print_skipped = false;
2826 } else if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED_SKIPPED) {
2827 print_passed = false;
2828 print_failed = true;
2829 print_skipped = true;
2830 }
2831
2832 //Build test identifier with padding: Suite.Test.....
2833 char test_identifier[__CLOVE_STRING_LENGTH];
2834 __clove_string_sprintf(test_identifier, __CLOVE_STRING_LENGTH, "%s.%s", suite->name, test->name);
2835 __clove_string_pad_right(test_identifier, __CLOVE_STRING_LENGTH, report->max_suite_and_test_name_size);
2836
2837 if (print_passed && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_PASSED) {
2838 float millis = (float)(__clove_time_to_nanos(&(test->duration))) / (float)__CLOVE_TIME_TRANSL_NANOS_PER_MILLIS;
2839 int decimal = millis > 1.f ? 0 : 3;
2840
2841 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s %0*zu) %s%s (%.*f ms)\n",
2842 report->labels.info,
2843 report->max_test_digits, test_number,
2844 test_identifier,
2845 report->labels.pass,
2846 decimal, millis);
2847 }
2848 else if (print_failed && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED) {
2849 char msg[__CLOVE_STRING_LENGTH] = "FAILURE but NO MESSAGE!!!";
2850
2851 if (test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_FAIL) {
2852 __clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%s", "A FAIL assertion was met!");
2853 }
2854 else {
2855 __CLOVE_SWITCH_BEG(test->issue.data_type)
2856 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_BOOL) {
2857 const char* exp = test->issue.expected._bool ? "true" : "false";
2858 const char* act = test->issue.actual._bool ? "true" : "false";
2859 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "expected [%s] but was [%s]", exp, act);
2860 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%s");
2861 }
2862 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_CHAR) {
2863 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2864 const char exp = test->issue.expected._char;
2865 const char act = test->issue.actual._char;
2866 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%c] but was [%c]", non, exp, act);
2867 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%c");
2868 }
2869 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_INT) {
2870 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2871 const int exp = test->issue.expected._int;
2872 const int act = test->issue.actual._int;
2873 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%d] but was [%d]", non, exp, act);
2874 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%d");
2875 }
2876 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_UINT) {
2877 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2878 const unsigned int exp = test->issue.expected._uint;
2879 const unsigned int act = test->issue.actual._uint;
2880 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%u] but was [%u]", non, exp, act);
2881 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%u");
2882 }
2883 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_LONG) {
2884 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2885 const long exp = test->issue.expected._long;
2886 const long act = test->issue.actual._long;
2887 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%ld] but was [%ld]", non, exp, act);
2888 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%ld");
2889 }
2890 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_ULONG) {
2891 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2892 const unsigned long exp = test->issue.expected._ulong;
2893 const unsigned long act = test->issue.actual._ulong;
2894 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%lu] but was [%lu]", non, exp, act);
2895 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%lu");
2896 }
2897 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_LLONG) {
2898 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2899 const long long exp = test->issue.expected._llong;
2900 const long long act = test->issue.actual._llong;
2901 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%lld] but was [%lld]", non, exp, act);
2902 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%lld");
2903 }
2904 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_ULLONG) {
2905 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2906 const unsigned long long exp = test->issue.expected._ullong;
2907 const unsigned long long act = test->issue.actual._ullong;
2908 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%llu] but was [%llu]", non, exp, act);
2909 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%llu");
2910 }
2911 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_SIZET) {
2912 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2913 const size_t exp = test->issue.expected._sizet;
2914 const size_t act = test->issue.actual._sizet;
2915 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%zu] but was [%zu]", non, exp, act);
2916 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%zu");
2917 }
2918 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_FLOAT) {
2919 const float exp = test->issue.expected._float;
2920 const float act = test->issue.actual._float;
2921 char format[6] = {0}; //Example: %.NNf
2922 __clove_string_sprintf(format, sizeof(format), "%%.%df", test->issue.floating_precision);
2923 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, format);
2924 }
2925 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_DOUBLE) {
2926 const double exp = test->issue.expected._double;
2927 const double act = test->issue.actual._double;
2928 char format[6] = {0}; //Example: %.NNf
2929 __clove_string_sprintf(format, sizeof(format), "%%.%df", test->issue.floating_precision);
2930 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, format);
2931 }
2932 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_STRING) {
2933 const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2934 const char* exp = test->issue.expected._string;
2935 const char* act = test->issue.actual._string;
2936
2937 const size_t max_len = 16;
2938 const size_t exp_len = __clove_string_length(exp);
2939 const size_t act_len = __clove_string_length(act);
2940
2941 if (exp_len <= max_len && act_len <= max_len) {
2942 char* exp_escaped = __clove_string_escape(exp);
2943 char* act_escaped = __clove_string_escape(act);
2944 __clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected \"%s\" but was \"%s\"", non, exp_escaped, act_escaped);
2945 __clove_memory_free(exp_escaped);
2946 __clove_memory_free(act_escaped);
2947 }
2948 else {
2949 char exp_short[16];
2950 char act_short[16];
2951 __clove_report_pretty_string_ellipse(exp, exp_len, act, act_len, exp_short, act_short, 16);
2952
2953 char* exp_escaped = __clove_string_escape(exp_short);
2954 char* act_escaped = __clove_string_escape(act_short);
2955 __clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%zu]\"%s\" but was [%zu]\"%s\"", non, exp_len, exp_escaped, act_len, act_escaped);
2956 __clove_memory_free(exp_escaped);
2957 __clove_memory_free(act_escaped);
2958 }
2959 }
2960 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_PTR) {
2961 //const char* non = test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_EQ ? "" : "not ";
2962 const void* exp = test->issue.expected._ptr;
2963 const void* act = test->issue.actual._ptr;
2964 //__clove_string_sprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "%sexpected [%p] but was [%p]", non, exp, act);
2965 __PRETTY_PRINT_FAIL_ASSERT_MSG(msg, sizeof(msg), test->issue.assert, exp, act, "%p");
2966 }
2967 __CLOVE_SWITCH_END()
2968 }
2969
2970 const char* file_path = test->file_name;
2971 if (report->params->tests_base_path) {
2972 file_path = __clove_path_relative(test->file_name, report->params->tests_base_path);
2973 }
2974
2975 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s %0*zu) %s%s %s:%zu: %s\n",
2976 report->labels.erro,
2977 report->max_test_digits, test_number,
2978 test_identifier,
2979 report->labels.fail,
2980 file_path, test->issue.line, msg);
2981 }
2982 else if (print_skipped && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_SKIPPED) {
2983
2984 const char* file_path = test->file_name;
2985 if (report->params->tests_base_path) {
2986 file_path = __clove_path_relative(test->file_name, report->params->tests_base_path);
2987 }
2988
2989 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s %0*zu) %s%s %s:%zu: %s\n",
2990 report->labels.warn,
2991 report->max_test_digits, test_number,
2992 test_identifier,
2993 report->labels.skip,
2994 file_path, test->funct_line, "Missing assertion!");
2995 }
2996}

2998void __clove_report_pretty_string_ellipse(
2999 const char* exp, size_t exp_len,
3000 const char* act, size_t act_len,
3001 char* exp_short, char* act_short, size_t short_size)
3002{
3003 size_t iter_len = exp_len < act_len ? exp_len : act_len;
3004 if (iter_len == 0) {
3005 __clove_string_ellipse(exp, exp_len, 0, exp_short, short_size);
3006 __clove_string_ellipse(act, act_len, 0, act_short, short_size);
3007 return;
3008 }
3009
3010 for (size_t i = 0; i < iter_len; ++i) {
3011 if (exp[i] != act[i]) {
3012 __clove_string_ellipse(exp, exp_len, i, exp_short, short_size);
3013 __clove_string_ellipse(act, act_len, i, act_short, short_size);
3014 return;
3015 }
3016 }
3017
3018 //Scenario where the shortest one is the like the "prefix" of the longest one
3019 __clove_string_ellipse(exp, exp_len, iter_len-1, exp_short, short_size);
3020 __clove_string_ellipse(act, act_len, iter_len-1, act_short, short_size);
3021}

3074void __clove_report_run_tests_csv_end_test(__clove_report_t* _this, __clove_suite_t* suite, __clove_test_t* test, size_t test_number) {
3075 __CLOVE_UNUSED_VAR(test_number);
3076
3077 __clove_report_run_tests_csv_t* report = (__clove_report_run_tests_csv_t*)_this;
3078
3079 bool print_passed = false;
3080 bool print_failed = false;
3081 bool print_skipped = false;
3082 if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__PASSED_FAILED_SKIPPED) {
3083 print_passed = true;
3084 print_failed = true;
3085 print_skipped = true;
3086 } else if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED) {
3087 print_passed = false;
3088 print_failed = true;
3089 print_skipped = false;
3090 } else if (report->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED_SKIPPED) {
3091 print_passed = false;
3092 print_failed = true;
3093 print_skipped = true;
3094 }
3095
3097 if (print_passed && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_PASSED) {
3098 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s,%s,%s,%llu,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s\n",
3099 suite->name, test->name, test->result, __clove_time_to_nanos(&(test->duration)),"","","","","","");
3100 }
3101 else if (print_failed && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED) {
3102 const char* data_type = (test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_FAIL) ? "" : test->issue.data_type;
3103 const char* file_name = __clove_path_relative(test->file_name, report->params->tests_base_path);
3104
3105 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%zu,%s,%s,",
3106 suite->name, test->name, test->result, "",file_name,test->issue.line, test->issue.assert, data_type);
3107
3108 __clove_report_run_tests_csv_print_data(report, test, &test->issue.expected);
3109 report->stream->writef(report->stream, ",");
3110 __clove_report_run_tests_csv_print_data(report, test, &test->issue.actual);
3111 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "\n");
3112 }
3113 else if (print_skipped && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_SKIPPED) {
3114 const char* file_name = __clove_path_relative(test->file_name, report->params->tests_base_path);
3115
3116 report->stream->writef(report->stream, "%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%zu,%s,%s,%s,%s\n",
3117 suite->name, test->name, test->result,"",file_name,test->funct_line,"","","","");
3118 }
3119}

3123 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%s", "");

3138 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_LLONG)

3140 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_ULLONG)
3141 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%llu", data->_ullong);
3142 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_SIZET)
3143 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%zu", data->_sizet);
3144 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_FLOAT)

3146 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_DOUBLE)
3147 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%.*f", test->issue.floating_precision, data->_double);

3156 }

3223void __clove_report_json_end(__clove_report_t* _this, size_t passed, size_t skipped, size_t failed) {
3224 __clove_report_json_t* instance = (__clove_report_json_t*)_this;
3225
3226 if (!instance->is_reporting_enabled) {
3227 instance->is_reporting_enabled = true;
3228
3229 size_t suite_count = __clove_vector_count(&instance->cached_suites);
3230 size_t test_number = 0;
3231
3232 bool report_failed = false;
3233 bool report_skipped = false;
3234 if (instance->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED) {
3235 report_failed = true;
3236 report_skipped = false;
3237 } else if (instance->params->report_detail == __CLOVE_REPORT_DETAIL__FAILED_SKIPPED) {
3238 report_failed = true;
3239 report_skipped = true;
3240 }
3241
3242 for(size_t suite_index=0; suite_index < suite_count; ++suite_index) {
3243 __clove_suite_t* suite = *(__clove_suite_t**)__clove_vector_get(&instance->cached_suites, suite_index);
3244 bool has_failed = report_failed && suite->issue.failed_count > 0;
3245 bool has_skipped = report_skipped && suite->issue.skipped_count > 0;
3246 if (!has_failed && !has_skipped) continue;
3247
3248 instance->suite_tests_number = 0;
3249 if (has_failed) instance->suite_tests_number += suite->issue.failed_count;
3250 if (has_skipped) instance->suite_tests_number += suite->issue.skipped_count;
3251
3252 __clove_report_json_begin_suite(_this, suite, suite_index);
3253
3254 for(size_t test_index=0; test_index < __clove_vector_count(&suite->tests); ++test_index) {
3255 __clove_test_t* test = (__clove_test_t*)__clove_vector_get(&suite->tests, test_index);
3256 bool failed_case = report_failed && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED;
3257 bool skipped_case = report_skipped && test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_SKIPPED;
3258 if (!failed_case && !skipped_case) continue;
3259
3260 __clove_report_json_end_test(_this, suite, test, ++test_number);
3261 }
3262
3263 __clove_report_json_end_suite(_this, suite, suite_index);
3264 }
3265 }
3266
3267 //Write overall results
3268 const char* status = "UNKNOWN";
3269 if (passed == instance->test_count) status = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_PASSED;
3270 else if (failed > 0) status = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED;
3271 else if (skipped > 0) status = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_SKIPPED;
3272
3273 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t},\n"); //suites
3274 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\"test_passed\" : %zu,\n", passed);
3275 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\"test_skipped\" : %zu,\n", skipped);
3276 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\"test_failed\" : %zu,\n", failed);
3277 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\"status\" : \"%s\"\n", status);
3278 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t}\n"); //result
3279 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "}"); //object
3280
3281 instance->stream->close(instance->stream);
3282}
3283
3284void __clove_report_json_print_data(__clove_report_json_t* instance, __clove_test_t* test, __clove_generic_u* data) {
3285 if (test->issue.assert == __CLOVE_ASSERT_FAIL) {
3286 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%s", "");
3287 } else {
3288 __CLOVE_SWITCH_BEG(test->issue.data_type)
3289 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_BOOL)
3290 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%s", data->_bool ? "true" : "false");
3291 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_CHAR)
3292 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%c", data->_char);
3293 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_INT)
3294 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%d", data->_int);
3295 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_UINT)
3296 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%u", data->_uint);
3297 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_LONG)
3298 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%ld", data->_long);
3299 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_ULONG)
3300 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%lu", data->_ulong);
3301 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_LLONG)
3302 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%lld", data->_llong);
3303 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_ULLONG)
3304 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%llu", data->_ullong);
3305 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_SIZET)
3306 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%zu", data->_sizet);
3307 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_FLOAT)
3308 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%.*f", test->issue.floating_precision, data->_float);
3309 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_DOUBLE)
3310 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%.*f", test->issue.floating_precision, data->_double);
3311 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_STRING) {
3312 char* escaped = __clove_string_escape(data->_string);
3313 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%s", escaped);
3314 __clove_memory_free(escaped);
3315 }
3316 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_GENERIC_PTR)
3317 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "%p", data->_ptr);
3318 __CLOVE_SWITCH_END()
3319 }
3320}

3350void __clove_report_json_end_test(__clove_report_t* _this, __clove_suite_t* suite, __clove_test_t* test, size_t test_number) {
3351 __CLOVE_UNUSED_VAR(test_number);
3352
3353 __clove_report_json_t* instance = (__clove_report_json_t*)_this;
3354 if (!instance->is_reporting_enabled) return;
3355
3356 if (instance->is_first_suite_test) {
3357 const char* file_path = __clove_path_relative(test->file_name, instance->params->tests_base_path);
3358 char* escaped_file = __clove_string_strdup(file_path);
3359 __clove_string_replace_char(escaped_file, '\\', '/');
3360
3361 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\"%s\" : {\n", instance->current_suite->name);
3362 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\"file\" : \"%s\",\n", escaped_file);
3363 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\"tests\" : {\n");
3364 instance->suite_tests_counter = 0;
3365
3366 __clove_memory_free(escaped_file);
3367 instance->is_first_suite_test = false;
3368 }
3369
3370 instance->suite_tests_counter++;
3371 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\"%s\" : {\n", test->name);
3372 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"status\" : \"%s\",\n", test->result);
3373 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"duration\" : %llu", __clove_time_to_nanos(&(test->duration)));
3374 if (test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED) {
3375 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, ",\n");
3376 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"line\" : %zu,\n", test->issue.line);
3377 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"assert\" : \"%s\"", test->issue.assert);
3378 if (test->issue.assert != __CLOVE_ASSERT_FAIL) {
3379 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, ",\n");
3380 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"type\" : \"%s\",\n", test->issue.data_type);
3381 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"expected\" : \"");
3382 __clove_report_json_print_data(instance, test, &(test->issue.expected));
3383 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\",\n");
3384
3385 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"actual\" : \"");
3386 __clove_report_json_print_data(instance, test, &(test->issue.actual));
3387 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\"\n");
3388 } else {
3389 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\n");
3390 }
3391 } else if (test->result == __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_SKIPPED) {
3392 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, ",\n");
3393 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t\t\"line\" : %zu\n", test->funct_line);
3394 } else {
3395 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\n");
3396 }
3397 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t\t}");
3398
3399 size_t suite_total_tests = suite->test_count; //realtime scenario
3400 if (!instance->is_realtime_scenario) suite_total_tests = instance->suite_tests_number;
3401
3402 if (instance->suite_tests_counter < suite_total_tests) {
3403 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, ",\n");
3404 }
3405 else {
3406 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\n");
3407 instance->stream->writef(instance->stream, "\t\t\t\t}\n"); //close "tests"
3408 }
3409}

3658bool __clove_symbols_function_validate(__clove_string_view_t* suite, __clove_string_view_t* type, __clove_string_view_t* name, __clove_symbols_context_t* context) {
3659 if (__clove_vector_is_empty(context->includes) && __clove_vector_is_empty(context->excludes)) return true;
3660 if (!__clove_string_view_strequals(type, "20")) return true;
3661
3662 //Includes win over Excludes
3663 if (!__clove_vector_is_empty(context->includes)) {
3664 for(size_t i=0; i < __clove_vector_count(context->includes); ++i) {
3665 __clove_test_expr_t* expr = (__clove_test_expr_t*)__clove_vector_get(context->includes, i);
3666 if (__clove_test_expr_validate(expr, suite, name)) return true;
3667 }
3668 return false;
3669 }
3670
3671 if (!__clove_vector_is_empty(context->excludes)) {
3672 for(size_t i=0; i < __clove_vector_count(context->excludes); ++i) {
3673 __clove_test_expr_t* expr = (__clove_test_expr_t*)__clove_vector_get(context->excludes, i);
3674 if (__clove_test_expr_validate(expr, suite, name)) return false;
3675 }
3676 return true;
3677 }
3678 return true;
3679}

3681void __clove_symbols_function_collect(__clove_symbols_function_t exported_funct, __clove_symbols_context_t* context) {
3682 /* Examples
3683 __clove_sym___MySuite___11_setuponce
3684 __clove_sym___MySuite___12_teardownonce
3685 __clove_sym___MySuite___13_setup
3686 __clove_sym___MySuite___14_teardown
3687 __clove_sym___MySuite___20_MyTest01
3688 __clove_sym___MySuite___20_MyTest02
3689 */
3690 static const char* end_suite_separator = "___";
3691 static int end_suite_separator_length = 3;
3692 //static const char* test_separator = "20_";
3693 //static int test_separator_length = 3;
3694
3695 static __clove_suite_t last_suite_temp; //just used as temporary data storage
3696 static __clove_suite_t* last_suite_ptr = NULL;
3697 static __clove_string_view_t suite_name_view = { NULL, 0 };
3698
3699 const char* test_full_name = exported_funct.name;
3700 const char* begin_suite_name = test_full_name + context->prefix_length;
3701 const char* end_suite_name = __clove_string_strstr(begin_suite_name, end_suite_separator) - 1;
3702
3703 __clove_string_view_t suite_vw = __clove_string_view_from_be(begin_suite_name, end_suite_name);
3704 __clove_string_view_t type_vw = __clove_string_view_from_len(end_suite_name + 1 + end_suite_separator_length, 2);
3705 __clove_string_view_t name_vw = __clove_string_view_from_str(__clove_string_view_end(&type_vw) + 2);
3706
3707 bool pass = __clove_symbols_function_validate(&suite_vw, &type_vw, &name_vw, context);
3708 if (!pass) return;
3709
3710 //if suite changes, then start collecting temporary suite data, waiting for a first test to be found
3711 if (suite_name_view.begin == NULL || !__clove_string_view_equals(&suite_vw, &suite_name_view)) {
3712 suite_name_view = suite_vw;
3713 last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup_once = NULL;
3714 last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown_once = NULL;
3715 last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup = NULL;
3716 last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown = NULL;
3717 last_suite_temp.test_count = 0;
3718 }
3719
3720 if (__clove_string_view_strequals(&type_vw, "11")) {
3721 last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup_once = exported_funct.fun_ptr;
3722 }
3723 else if (__clove_string_view_strequals(&type_vw, "12")) {
3724 last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown_once = exported_funct.fun_ptr;
3725 }
3726 else if (__clove_string_view_strequals(&type_vw, "13")) {
3727 last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup = exported_funct.fun_ptr;
3728 }
3729 else if (__clove_string_view_strequals(&type_vw, "14")) {
3730 last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown = exported_funct.fun_ptr;
3731 }
3732 else if (__clove_string_view_strequals(&type_vw, "20")) {
3733 if (last_suite_temp.test_count == 0) {
3734 last_suite_temp.test_count = 1; //just to record that at least one test case has been found
3735
3736 last_suite_ptr = (__clove_suite_t*)__clove_vector_add_slot(&context->suites);
3737 last_suite_ptr->name = __clove_string_view_as_string(&suite_name_view);
3738 if (last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup_once) last_suite_ptr->fixtures.setup_once = last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup_once;
3739 if (last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown_once) last_suite_ptr->fixtures.teardown_once = last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown_once;
3740 if (last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup) last_suite_ptr->fixtures.setup = last_suite_temp.fixtures.setup;
3741 if (last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown) last_suite_ptr->fixtures.teardown = last_suite_temp.fixtures.teardown;
3742 context->suites_count++;
3743 }
3744
3745 __clove_test_t* test = (__clove_test_t*)__clove_vector_add_slot(&last_suite_ptr->tests);
3746 //Switched to string allocation to make test structs independent of the source memory
3747 //test->name = test_name + test_separator_length;
3748 test->name = __clove_string_view_as_string(&name_vw);
3749 test->funct = (void (*)(__clove_test_t*))exported_funct.fun_ptr;
3750 last_suite_ptr->test_count++;
3751 context->tests_count++;
3752 }
3753}

3757PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY __clove_symbols_win_get_export_table_from(HMODULE module) {
3758 // Start at the base of the module. The MS-DOS stub begins there.
3759 PBYTE base = (PBYTE)module;
3760 PIMAGE_DOS_HEADER mds = (PIMAGE_DOS_HEADER)module;
3761
3762 PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS nt_header = (PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS)(base + mds->e_lfanew);
3763 if (IMAGE_NT_SIGNATURE != nt_header->Signature) {
3764 // Bad signature -- invalid image or module handle
3765 return NULL;
3766 }
3767
3768 // Get the COFF file header.
3769 //PIMAGE_FILE_HEADER cfh = &nt_header->FileHeader;
3770
3771 // Get the "optional" header (it's not actually optional for executables).
3772 PIMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER oh = &nt_header->OptionalHeader;
3773
3774 // Finally, get the export directory table.
3775 if (IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT >= oh->NumberOfRvaAndSizes) {
3776 // This image doesn't have an export directory table.
3777 return NULL;
3778 }
3779 DWORD rva = oh->DataDirectory[IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT].VirtualAddress;
3780 PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY edt = (PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY)(base + rva);
3781 return edt;
3782}

3784int __clove_symbols_for_each_function_by_prefix(__clove_symbols_context_t* context, __clove_symbols_function_action action) {
3785 HMODULE module = GetModuleHandle(0);
3786 PIMAGE_EXPORT_DIRECTORY export_dir = __clove_symbols_win_get_export_table_from(module);
3787 if (!export_dir) {
3788 return 1;
3789 }
3790
3791 //Note: Don't know why if there is no exported function results NumberOfNames = 64. NumberOfFunctions = 0 instead.
3792 // So checking both counters to be sure if there is any exported function
3793 if (export_dir->NumberOfNames == 0 || export_dir->NumberOfFunctions == 0) {
3794 return 1;
3795 }
3796
3797 PBYTE base_addr = (PBYTE)module;
3798 //DWORD names_count = export_dir->NumberOfNames;
3799 PDWORD names_ptr = (PDWORD)(base_addr + export_dir->AddressOfNames);
3800 DWORD ordinal_base_number = export_dir->Base;
3801 PWORD ordinals_ptr = (PWORD)(base_addr + export_dir->AddressOfNameOrdinals); //ordinal offset from base ordinal
3802 PDWORD functs_address_ptr = (PDWORD)(base_addr + export_dir->AddressOfFunctions);
3803
3804 const char* prefix = context->prefix;
3805 size_t prefix_length = context->prefix_length;
3806
3807 //Takes advantage of symbols are lexically sorted.
3808 //And also that prefix starting with "__" will come first. So no need to start a binary search
3809 unsigned char match_ongoing = 0;
3810 for (size_t i = 0; i < export_dir->NumberOfNames; ++i)
3811 {
3812 char* each_name = (char*)(base_addr + names_ptr[i]);
3813 unsigned long each_ordinal = ordinal_base_number + ordinals_ptr[i];
3814 unsigned long* each_funct_addr = (PDWORD)(base_addr + functs_address_ptr[each_ordinal - ordinal_base_number]);
3815 //printf("%lu) %s [0x%p]\n", each_ordinal, each_name, each_funct_addr);
3816
3817 if (strncmp(prefix, each_name, prefix_length) == 0) {
3818 if (!match_ongoing) match_ongoing = 1;
3819 __clove_symbols_function_t funct;
3820 funct.name = each_name;
3821 funct.obj_ptr = each_funct_addr;
3822 action(funct, context);
3823 }
3824 else {
3825 //At the first failure, if match was ongoing then there are no more symbol with that prefix
3826 if (match_ongoing) break;
3827 }
3828 }
3829 return 0;
3830}

3896struct load_command* __clove_symbols_macos_find_command(struct mach_header_64* header, uint32_t cmd) {
3897 struct load_command* lc = (struct load_command*)((uint64_t)header + sizeof(struct mach_header_64));
3898 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < header->ncmds; i++) {
3899 if (lc->cmd == cmd) {
3900 return lc;
3901 }
3902 lc = (struct load_command*)((uint64_t)lc + lc->cmdsize);
3903 }
3904 return NULL;
3905}

3907int __clove_symbols_for_each_function_by_prefix(__clove_symbols_context_t* context, __clove_symbols_function_action action) {
3908 const char* module_path = __clove_utils_get_exec_abs_path();
3909
3910 __clove_symbols_macos_module_t module;
3911 if (__clove_symbols_macos_open_module_handle(module_path, &module) != 0) { return 1; };
3912
3913 //Handling Mach-o file format x86_64 (little endian). This should works both for Intel and M1 cpus with 64 bits architecture
3914 uint32_t magic_number = *(uint32_t*)module.handle;
3915 if (magic_number != MH_MAGIC_64) {
3916 puts("Current executable format is not supported (it's not Mach-o 64bit little-endian!");
3917 return 2;
3918 }
3919
3920 struct mach_header_64* header = (struct mach_header_64*)module.handle;
3921 struct load_command* symbol_lc = __clove_symbols_macos_find_command(header, LC_SYMTAB);
3922 struct symtab_command* symbol_cmd = (struct symtab_command*)symbol_lc;
3923
3924 struct nlist_64* symbol_table_64 = (struct nlist_64*)((uint64_t)header + symbol_cmd->symoff);
3925 char* str_table = (char*)header + symbol_cmd->stroff;
3926 //symbol_cmd->nsyms #number of symbols in the symbol table
3927
3928 //Loading Dynamic Symbol table to scan only for external symbols symbols in the Symbol Table
3929 struct load_command* dynsymbol_lc = __clove_symbols_macos_find_command(header, LC_DYSYMTAB);
3930 struct dysymtab_command* dysymbol_cmd = (struct dysymtab_command*)dynsymbol_lc;
3931 uint32_t external_symbol_start_index = dysymbol_cmd->iextdefsym;
3932 uint32_t external_symbol_end_index = external_symbol_start_index + dysymbol_cmd->nextdefsym - 1U;
3933
3934 const char* prefix = context->prefix;
3935 const size_t prefix_length = context->prefix_length;
3936 uint8_t match_ongoing = 0;
3937 for (uint32_t i = external_symbol_start_index; i <= external_symbol_end_index; i++) {
3938 struct nlist_64* sym = &symbol_table_64[i];
3939 uint32_t table_index = sym->n_un.n_strx;
3940 char* each_name = &str_table[table_index + 1]; //macho add one '_' before each symbol, so with +1 we want to skip it.
3941 void* each_funct_addr = (void*)(sym->n_value + module.address); //n_value = offset address within TEXT segment (includes base addr of the TEXT segment)
3942
3943 //Symbols seems to be "locally" sorted, so all clove external functions seems to be next to each other and sorted
3944 if (strncmp(prefix, each_name, prefix_length) == 0) {
3945 if (!match_ongoing) {
3946 match_ongoing = 1;
3947 }
3948 //__clove_symbols_function_t funct = { each_name, each_funct_addr };
3949 __clove_symbols_function_t funct;
3950 funct.name = each_name;
3951 funct.obj_ptr = each_funct_addr;
3952 action(funct, context);
3953 }
3954 else {
3955 //At the first failure, if match was ongoing then there are no more symbol with that prefix
3956 if (match_ongoing) {
3957 break;
3958 }
3959 }
3960
3961 }
3962 __clove_symbols_macos_close_module_handle(&module);
3963 return 0;
3964}

3980int __clove_symbols_lixux_dl_callback(struct dl_phdr_info* info, size_t size, void* data)
3981{
3982 __CLOVE_UNUSED_VAR(size);
3983
3984 #ifdef __GNUC__
3985 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
3986 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wpedantic" //Disable pedantic
3987 #endif
3988 //Preventing GCC pedantic from emitting warning: "ISO C forbids conversion of function pointer to object pointer type"
3989 const char* cb = (const char*)&__clove_symbols_lixux_dl_callback;
3990 #ifdef __GNUC__
3991 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
3992 #endif
3993
3994 const char* base = (const char*)info->dlpi_addr;
3995 const ElfW(Phdr)* first_load = NULL;
3996
3997 for (int j = 0; j < info->dlpi_phnum; j++) {
3998 const ElfW(Phdr)* phdr = &info->dlpi_phdr[j];
3999
4000 if (phdr->p_type == PT_LOAD) {
4001 const char* beg = base + phdr->p_vaddr;
4002 const char* end = beg + phdr->p_memsz;
4003
4004 if (first_load == NULL) first_load = phdr;
4005 if (beg <= cb && cb < end) {
4006 // Found PT_LOAD that "covers" callback().
4007 //printf("ELF header is at %p, image linked at 0x%zx, relocation: 0x%zx\n", base + first_load->p_vaddr, first_load->p_vaddr, info->dlpi_addr);
4008 uintptr_t* addr_ptr = (uintptr_t*)data;
4009 *addr_ptr = info->dlpi_addr;
4010 return 1;
4011 }
4012 }
4013 }
4014 return 0;
4015}

4058/*
4059 * Compare two functions by their name
4060 * Return negative if name1 is lesser than name2
4061 * Return positive if name1 is greater than name1
4062 * Return zero if name1 and name2 are equals
4063 */
4064int __clove_symbols_funct_name_comparator(void* f1, void* f2) {
4065 __clove_symbols_function_t* funct1 = (__clove_symbols_function_t*)f1;
4066 __clove_symbols_function_t* funct2 = (__clove_symbols_function_t*)f2;
4067 return strcmp(funct1->name, funct2->name);
4068}

4070int __clove_symbols_for_each_function_by_prefix(__clove_symbols_context_t* context, __clove_symbols_function_action action) {
4071 const char* module_path = __clove_utils_get_exec_abs_path();
4072
4073 __clove_symbols_lixux_module_t module;
4074 if (__clove_symbols_lixux_open_module_handle(module_path, &module) != 0) { return 1; }
4075
4076 //Check Elf header to be 64 bit little endian
4077 unsigned char* magic = (unsigned char*)module.handle;
4078 bool is_elf = (magic[0] == 0x7f && magic[1] == 0x45 && magic[2] == 0x4c && magic[3] == 0x46);
4079 bool is_64 = (magic[4] == 0x02); //0x01 is 32 bit
4080 bool is_little = (magic[5] == 0x01); //0x02 is big endian
4081
4082 if (!(is_elf && is_64 && is_little)) {
4083 puts("Current executable format is not supported (it's not ELF 64bit little-endian!)");
4084 return 2;
4085 }
4086
4087 Elf64_Ehdr* header = (Elf64_Ehdr*)module.handle;
4088
4089 Elf64_Shdr* sections = (Elf64_Shdr*)((uint64_t)header + header->e_shoff);
4090 size_t section_count = header->e_shnum;
4091
4092 Elf64_Sym* symbol_table = NULL;
4093 Elf64_Shdr* symbol_table_section = NULL;
4094 for (size_t i = 0; i < section_count; ++i) {
4095 if (sections[i].sh_type == SHT_SYMTAB) {
4096 symbol_table = (Elf64_Sym*)((uint64_t)header + sections[i].sh_offset);
4097 symbol_table_section = &sections[i];
4098 break;
4099 }
4100 }
4101
4102 Elf64_Shdr* name_table_section = &sections[symbol_table_section->sh_link];
4103 char* symbol_name_table = (char*)((uint64_t)header + name_table_section->sh_offset);
4104
4105 size_t symbol_count = symbol_table_section->sh_size / symbol_table_section->sh_entsize;
4106
4107 //Vector could be replaced with a sorted tree to sort while scanning for clove functions
4108 __clove_vector_t clove_functions;
4109 __clove_vector_params_t params = __clove_vector_params_defaulted(sizeof(__clove_symbols_function_t));
4110 __clove_vector_init(&clove_functions, &params);
4111
4112 const char* prefix = context->prefix;
4113 size_t prefix_length = context->prefix_length;
4114
4115 for (size_t i = 0; i < symbol_count; ++i) {
4116 Elf64_Sym* sym = &symbol_table[i];
4117 if (ELF64_ST_TYPE(sym->st_info) == STT_FUNC) {
4118 size_t name_index = sym->st_name;
4119 char* sym_name = symbol_name_table + name_index;
4120 if (!strncmp(sym_name, prefix, prefix_length)) {
4121 __clove_symbols_function_t* each_funct = (__clove_symbols_function_t*)__clove_vector_add_slot(&clove_functions);
4122 each_funct->name = sym_name;
4123 each_funct->obj_ptr = (void*)(module.address + sym->st_value);
4124 }
4125 }
4126 }
4127
4128 //Sort Symbols Alphanumeric ascendant
4129 __clove_vector_sort(&clove_functions, __clove_symbols_funct_name_comparator);
4130
4131 for (size_t i = 0; i < __clove_vector_count(&clove_functions); ++i)
4132 {
4133 __clove_symbols_function_t* each_funct = (__clove_symbols_function_t*)__clove_vector_get(&clove_functions, i);
4134 action(*each_funct, context);
4135 }
4136 __clove_vector_free(&clove_functions);
4137 __clove_symbols_lixux_close_module_handle(&module);
4138 return 0;
4139}

4143 puts("Autodiscovery not yet implemented for this OS!!!");

4229int __clove_exec_suites(__clove_vector_t* suites, size_t test_count, __clove_report_t* report) {
4230 report->start(report, suites, test_count);
4231 size_t passed = 0;
4232 size_t failed = 0;
4233 size_t skipped = 0;
4234
4235 size_t test_start_counter = 1;
4236 __CLOVE_VECTOR_FOR(suites, __clove_suite_t, each_suite, i, {
4237 report->begin_suite(report, each_suite, i);
4238 __clove_exec_suite(each_suite, test_start_counter, &passed, &failed, &skipped, report);
4239 report->end_suite(report, each_suite, i);
4240 test_start_counter += each_suite->test_count;
4241 });
4242 report->end(report, passed, skipped, failed);
4243 return failed == 0 ? 0 : 1;
4244}

4246void __clove_exec_suite(__clove_suite_t* suite, size_t test_counter, size_t* passed, size_t* failed, size_t* skipped, __clove_report_t* report) {
4247 __clove_time_t suite_start = __clove_time_now();
4248 suite->fixtures.setup_once();
4249
4250 for (size_t i = 0; i < suite->test_count; i++) {
4251 __clove_test_t* each_test = (__clove_test_t*)__clove_vector_get(&suite->tests, i);
4252 each_test->result = __CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_SKIPPED;
4253
4254 __clove_time_t test_start = __clove_time_now();
4255 suite->fixtures.setup();
4256 each_test->funct(each_test);
4257 suite->fixtures.teardown();
4258 __clove_time_t test_end = __clove_time_now();
4259 each_test->duration = __clove_time_sub(&test_end, &test_start);
4260
4261 __CLOVE_SWITCH_BEG(each_test->result)
4262 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_PASSED) { (*passed)++; suite->issue.passed_count++; }
4263 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_FAILED) { (*failed)++; suite->issue.failed_count++; }
4264 __CLOVE_SWITCH_CASE(__CLOVE_TEST_RESULT_SKIPPED) { (*skipped)++; suite->issue.skipped_count++;}
4265 __CLOVE_SWITCH_END()
4266
4267 report->end_test(report, suite, each_test, test_counter + i);
4268 }
4269 suite->fixtures.teardown_once();
4270 __clove_time_t suite_end = __clove_time_now();
4271 suite->issue.duration = __clove_time_sub(&suite_end, &suite_start);
4272}
